properties.areaDesc: Southern Sacramento Valley; Northern Sacramento Valley; Central Sacramento Valley
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 29 at 2:07AM PST until March 1 at 8:00PM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Gusty North Wind Sunday...

.Strong northerly winds will develop on Sunday over the
Sacramento Valley as a low pressure system exits the area. Wind
begins to increase late in the morning, with the strongest wind
Sunday afternoon and evening. Highest wind speeds are expected
along over the northern Sacramento Valley. Wind speeds decrease
Sunday night, but remain breezy into Monday.

* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 40 to 45 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Northern Sacramento Valley, Central Sacramento Valley
and Southern Sacramento Valley Counties.

* WHEN...From 10 AM to 8 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Driving could be difficult, especially for
high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 8 PM PST SUNDAY
